   "source": [
    "# Part 3-1: RAG with ColPali using MCP + Claude Desktop\n",
    "\n",
    "**Important Notice**: The Elastic MCP Server (`mcp-server-elasticsearch`) operates on Node.js and cannot be directly executed within Jupyter Notebook. This notebook provides a comprehensive guide for installing and running the MCP Server, as well as configuring Claude Desktop. After running the initial setup cells in this notebook, you must execute the provided commands in your local environment (terminal) to set up and run the MCP Server for the demo.\n",
    "\n",
    "Follow the step-by-step guide below to configure the Elastic MCP Server and Claude Desktop, and perform a natural language search demo on the RVL-CDIP dataset used in the ColPali project. This demo showcases the Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) approach, where the MCP Server retrieves relevant documents (Retrieval) and the LLM in Claude Desktop generates responses based on the search results (Generation).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objective**: Set up the Elastic MCP Server, connect it with Claude Desktop, and implement a natural language search demo for the RVL-CDIP dataset in the ColPali project."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**[EN]** Load environment variables from `elastic.env` to retrieve connection details for Elasticsearch.<br>\n",
    "**[KR]** `elastic.env` 파일에서 환경 변수를 로드하여 Elasticsearch 연결 정보를 가져옵니다."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load environment variables from elastic.env\n",
    "dotenv_path = 'elastic.env'\n",
    "load_dotenv(dotenv_path=dotenv_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Retrieve ES_URL and ES_API_KEY (mapping from ELASTIC_HOST and ELASTIC_API_KEY if needed)\n",
    "ES_URL = os.getenv(\"ELASTIC_HOST\", os.getenv(\"ES_URL\", \"\"))\n",
    "ES_API_KEY = os.getenv(\"ELASTIC_API_KEY\", os.getenv(\"ES_API_KEY\", \"\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "if not ES_URL or not ES_API_KEY:\n",
    "    raise ValueError(f\"Please create an '{dotenv_path}' file and set ES_URL (or ELASTIC_HOST) and ES_API_KEY variables.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"ES_URL loaded: {ES_URL[:20]}... (partially hidden for security)\")\n",
    "print(f\"ES_API_KEY loaded: {ES_API_KEY[:5]}... (partially hidden for security)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**[EN]** Create a `package.json` file to define the MCP Server dependency and script for installation and execution.<br>\n",
    "**[KR]** MCP 서버 의존성과 설치 및 실행 스크립트를 정의하기 위해 `package.json` 파일을 생성합니다."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: Create package.json for MCP Server Installation\n",
    "import json\n",
    "package_json = {\n",
    "    \"name\": \"colpali-rag-demo\",\n",
    "    \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n",
    "    \"description\": \"ColPali RAG Demo with Elastic MCP Server\",\n",
    "    \"dependencies\": {\n",
    "        \"@elastic/mcp-server-elasticsearch\": \"latest\"\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"scripts\": {\n",
    "        \"start-mcp\": \"npx @elastic/mcp-server-elasticsearch\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "with open('package.json', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(package_json, f, indent=2)\n",
    "print(\"package.json created. Run 'npm install' in your terminal to install the MCP Server.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**[EN]** Follow the steps below in your terminal to install and run the MCP Server, configure Claude Desktop, and perform the natural language search demo.<br>\n",
    "**[KR]** 아래 단계를 터미널에서 따라 MCP 서버를 설치 및 실행하고, Claude Desktop을 설정하며, 자연어 검색 데모를 수행하세요."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 2 to 4: Setup and Demo Guide for MCP + Claude Desktop\n",
    "\n",
    "**Step 2: Install and Run MCP Server**\n",
    "1. Open a terminal in the project directory.\n",
    "2. Run the following command to install the MCP Server package:\n",
    "   ```
    "   npm install\n",
    "   ```\n",
    "3. Set environment variables using the values loaded from `elastic.env` (as shown above):\n",
    "   - For Mac/Unix:\n",
    "     ```
    "     export ES_URL=<your-elasticsearch-url>\n",
    "     export ES_API_KEY=<your-api-key>\n",
    "     ```\n",
    "   - For Windows:\n",
    "     ```
    "     set ES_URL=<your-elasticsearch-url>\n",
    "     set ES_API_KEY=<your-api-key>\n",
    "     ```\n",
    "   Replace `<your-elasticsearch-url>` and `<your-api-key>` with the values shown above.\n",
    "4. Run the MCP Server:\n",
    "   ```
    "   npm run start-mcp\n",
    "   ```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Step 3: Configure Claude Desktop**\n",
    "1. Open Claude Desktop App.\n",
    "2. Go to `Settings > Developer > MCP Servers` and click 'Edit Config'.\n",
    "3. Add the following to `claude_desktop_config.json` using the loaded environment variables:\n",
    "   ```
    "   {\n",
    "     \"mcpServers\": {\n",
    "       \"elasticsearch-mcp-server\": {\n",
    "         \"command\": \"npx\",\n",
    "         \"args\": [\"-y\", \"@elastic/mcp-server-elasticsearch\"],\n",
    "         \"env\": {\n",
    "           \"ES_URL\": \"<your-elasticsearch-url>\",\n",
    "           \"ES_API_KEY\": \"<your-api-key>\"\n",
    "         }\n",
    "       }\n",
    "     }\n",
    "   }\n",
    "   ```\n",
    "   Replace `<your-elasticsearch-url>` and `<your-api-key>` with the values loaded from `elastic.env` (as shown above).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Step 4: Perform Natural Language Search**\n",
    "1. Start a new conversation in Claude Desktop.\n",
    "2. Enter a natural language query, e.g., \"Show me invoices with handwritten notes from the RVL-CDIP dataset.\"\n",
    "3. Observe how the MCP Server retrieves relevant documents and the LLM generates a response based on the search results."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
